MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (apps/game-server/src/machines/cartridges/voting/|apps/game-server/src/machines/actions/l2-elimination|apps/game-server/src/machines/actions/l2-day-resolution)
MATCH_CONTENT: (eliminatedId|winnerId|openVoting|closeVoting|OPEN_VOTING|CLOSE_VOTING|VOTE_RESULT|computeElimination|resolveVote)
ADVISORY: |
  You are editing SERVER-SIDE voting logic. Key invariants (from
  apps/game-server/.claude/invariants/voting.md):

  - Every voting mechanism MUST eliminate exactly one player
  - eliminatedId must NEVER be null (tie-break by lowest silver; no votes → lowest silver)
  - Only exception: FINALS picks a winner instead
  - Result payload must include: tallies, per-voter picks, elimination outcome
  - Results publish immediately when voting closes — never delayed to night summary

  Client cartridges (apps/client/src/cartridges/voting/) render server-decided
  outcomes and CANNOT violate these invariants — this rule intentionally does
  not fire on client UI edits.
